{
  "texts": [
    "These are sophisticated functions of the brain that include language, imagination, perception, and planning.",
    "Metacognition, in contrast, is the consciousness and comprehension of one's own cognitive processes (Mahdavi, 2014).",
    "It is a level above cognition and involves \"thinking about thinking\" (Mahdavi, 2014).",
    "Metacognition empowers individuals to control their own learning by planning and monitoring their cognitive processes, checking progress, and adjusting strategies as necessary.",
    "Motivation is the third element of SRL and is arguably its driving force (Lehmann & I. Hähnlein et al., 2014)."
  ]
}